# .dockerignore — build-context filter for `roastery/Dockerfile`.
#
# Rationale: the roastery container build sets its context to the
# workspace root so cargo can resolve every workspace member at
# `cargo build -p roastery` time. That means the build context can be
# large; this file trims it to the union of:
#
#   - Workspace manifests (`Cargo.toml`, `Cargo.lock`, `rust-toolchain.toml`)
#   - The `.cargo/` config dir
#   - The `crates/` source tree (every member's `Cargo.toml` is part
#     of the workspace graph and must be present for resolution)
#   - The `roastery/` source tree
#   - The `xtask/` source tree (workspace member; manifest required
#     even though we don't link it into the binary)
#
# Everything else is excluded — `target/`, the bench harness, the
# `barback/` Java tree, the test corpus, docs, and the CI workflow
# tree do not contribute to the binary and would only inflate the
# context upload.
#
# Whitelist-style filtering: we exclude everything with `*`, then
# re-include the paths the Dockerfile actually reads. This is safer
# than enumerating excludes one-by-one because it fails closed —
# a new top-level dir doesn't accidentally end up in the context.

# Default-deny.
*

# Re-include workspace manifests + lockfile.
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
!rust-toolchain.toml

# Re-include `.cargo/` (cargo config; carries registry overrides and
# rustflags the build needs to pick up).
!.cargo/
!.cargo/**

# Re-include the crates the workspace declares as members. Every
# crate's `Cargo.toml` must be present for `cargo metadata` to
# resolve the workspace graph; the source must be present so the
# dependency-only build in Stage 1 has something to compile against.
!crates/
!crates/**

# Re-include the roastery binary's source.
!roastery/
!roastery/**

# Re-include the xtask workspace member's manifest + source.
!xtask/
!xtask/**

# Hard re-exclude anything we never want in the build context, even
# if a recursive include pulls it in. `target/` is the big one —
# host-side build artifacts would balloon the context by hundreds
# of MB and are useless inside the container.
target/
**/target/
.git/
**/.git/
.github/
.claude/
.tooling/
.idea/
.vscode/
**/*.tmp
**/*.swp

# Test corpora and bench inputs aren't needed for the binary build.
test-corpus/
bench/
barback/
docs/
schema/
proto/
tests/
